FONT FINDING (cross-layer, P1):
  - fonts.css imports 3 @font-face (300/400/500); built CSS DOES ship all 3 rules
    (corrected: earlier "1 @font-face" was a grep-line artifact — minified CSS is one line).
    BUT all 3 @font-face src url() resolve to ONE emitted asset: Inter-Light-<hash>.woff2.
  - ROOT CAUSE: all 3 src woff2 files are byte-identical (48432 bytes, md5 65850a37...) —
    Medium & Regular are copies of Light. Identical content → one content-hash → Vite emits
    one file and rewrites all 3 url() to it. document.fonts reports 300/400/500 "loaded" but
    all share the same (Light) outlines; weight 600 (keypad) faux-bolds from it.
  - IMPACT: D-004 (self-host genuine 300/400/500) only cosmetically met. Keys (intended 500) and
    pending-line (intended 400) render from Light outlines / browser synthesis. Display readout
    (300, AA-critical) IS genuine → no a11y/contrast regression.
